<h3 id="in-class-structure">In-class structure</h3>

<p>I‚Äôll begin class with a very brief discussion of the reading. This is not intended to be a substitute for having done the reading. Instead, the idea is to refresh your memory about what we‚Äôll be discussing in class today by working through an couple of examples.</p>

<p>We‚Äôll spend most of class time solving problems in the following format.</p>

<ul>
  <li>I‚Äôll put a problem on the board.</li>
  <li>You‚Äôll think about the problem by yourself for a couple of minutes.</li>
  <li>We‚Äôll vote on an answer to the problem.</li>
  <li>You‚Äôll have a few minutes to talk to your classmates about the problem.</li>
  <li>We‚Äôll vote again.</li>
  <li>I‚Äôll tell you how I‚Äôd solve the problem.</li>
</ul>

